Italy Lobby Group Sees Refineries Shutdown Risk, Corriere Says

-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 
2011-10-22T10:59:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/italy-lobby-group-sees-refineries-shutdown-risk-corriere-says.html
Pasquale De Vita, head of Italian
industry group Unione Petrolifera, said that four or five
refineries are “at risk” of being closed in  Italy , daily
 Corriere della Sera  reported.  The potential shutdowns may affect 1,500 jobs, De Vita told
Corriere in an interview. He declined to say which of the 16
refineries in Italy may be closed, adding that plans will be
discussed with the government at a meeting next week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Remondini in Milan at 
 cremondini@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  